==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''Δημήτηρ''' (''Demeter''), from '''[[Δή]]''' (''De''), an early form of '''[[Γή]]''' (''Ge'') "earth" + '''[[μήτηρ]]''' (''meter'') "mother".

===Proper Noun===
'''Demeter'''
{{wikipedia}}
#''(Greek Mythology)'' The goddess of the fertility of the [[Earth]] and [[harvest]]s, protector of marriage and social order; daughter of [[Cronos]] and [[Rhea]], mother to [[Persephone]]

